qas.question: If a work must include a degree of originality, what else must it contain to be protected?
What makes a copy of an original idea infringing?

answers.text: it copies that person's unique, tangible expression of the idea

qas.question: What limitation is only embodied in case law, rather than statues?
If a work must exclude a degree of originality, what else must it contain to be protected?
If a work must include a degree of originality, what else mustn't it contain to be protected?

plausible_answers.text: it copies that person's unique, tangible expression of the idea

qas.question: What makes a copy of an unoriginal idea infringing?
What limitation is only embodied in case law, and also in statues?
